summaries.short: (Season Three Finale). As Eric and Bill play out their end game with Russell, Sookie contemplates a life free of vampires.
summaries.full: (Season Three Finale). Eric grapples with his conscience while plotting his perfect revenge against Russell. Fed up with being 'vampire crack,' Sookie considers a new life without Bill--or any other vampire. Tara discovers some surprising news about Sam; Jason finds a new calling; Hoyt hopes for a future with Jessica, spurning Maxine's pleas to wed Summer.

summaries.short: Season Four Premiere. Sookie journeys away from Bon Temps; Eric and Bill try to win back the human public.
summaries.full: Season Four Premiere. Sookie journeys away from Bon Temps; Eric and Bill try to win back the human public; Jason learns that no good deed goes unpunished; Tara finds refuge in close quarters; Sam bonds with his own; Hoyt and Jessica debate the dinner menu; Jesus urges Lafayette to join a coven; Terry tries to alleviate Arlene's fears about the baby.

summaries.short: Bill tests the limits of Sookie's trust, again; Eric makes a deal with Russell; Sam embraces his dark side.
summaries.full: Bill tests the limits of Sookie's trust, again; Eric makes a deal with Russell; Jason tries to wrap his head around Crystal's revelation. Sam embraces his dark side; Hoyt and Jessica take their romance to the next level; with Holly's help, Arlene puts her future in the hands of a goddess; post V-trip, Lafayette struggles with new demons.

summaries.short: Bill warns Sookie about imminent dangers, while Eric lays low to avoid the wrath of Russell; Russell promises revenge on his enemies.
summaries.full: Bill warns Sookie about the dangers she will face. Jesus is intrigued by the mysterious qualities of V. Sam's fit of rage triggers dark memories. Eric takes precautions and fulfills a wish; Jason deals with the unexpected; Jessica is torn between Tommy and Hoyt. After communing with Talbot, Russell promises to extract vengeance on his enemies.

summaries.full: Sookie makes a deal with Eric, and reconnects with Alcide; Bill punishes an errant vampire and counsels a guilt-ridden Jessica; Jason is cast as a reluctant savior; Tommy eyes a scam and alienates Sam; Marnie flexes her newfound powers; Pam delivers an ultimatum to Lafayette, Tara and Jesus; Eric spoils Sookie's faerie reunion.

summaries.short: Bill uncovers Sookie's true identity; Eric finds safety in captivity; Russell takes his case to the people.
summaries.full: Nan Flanagan detours to Fangtasia to confront Eric; Russell vows revenge against his foes, vampire and human; Bill uncovers the truth about Sookie's true identity. Jason gets unexpected help as he goes up against Felton and Calvin; Tara encounters a new ally and an old tormenter; Hadley introduces Sookie to a new family member; Hoyt confronts his true feelings.
